pageContext.description: On each face are 2 small raised bosses like rivet heads, within a rectangular frame.
pageContext.patina: Thin black patina, rubbed off in places [enpossing?] yellow metal, with slight green stains.
pageContext.associations: Part of a hoard of 9 pieces comprising 4 whole and 2 broken socketed celts, 2 fragments of winged celts, and 1 gouge, also, parts of a cake of metal weighing 17 lbs. 6 oz.
pageContext.site: England,Greater London (Surrey),Coulsden,In a small wood. 400 ft. O.D. across the road from Coulsdon Court.,Found by workmen digging flints for road metal.,7th Jan. 1928
